<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-03T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/185:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from">Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-03T14:00:00+00:00">February 3, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 3—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>16. My telegram No. 14, January 29, 2 p.m. Four prisoners pardoned
                                this morning with customary condition that they leave the Balearic
                                Islands which does not preclude their living in Spain. Assured by
                                Minister of State that telephonic instructions would be sent to
                                Palma de Mallorca for their immediate release.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>